The paper deals with a game-semantic model of computation and its implementation using pushdown automata. This topic is closely related to formal languages and automata theory, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.FL and cs.TC. The paper also discusses the programming language PCF, which falls under the sub-category cs.PL. Additionally, the paper involves mathematical logic and proof theory, which are covered by the sub-category cs.LO. Finally, the paper discusses the computational power of different types of automata, which is related to the sub-category cs.CC.
